<< LOL! Nope, there aren't ferns of any kind in Utah. >>

In the Jemez mountains west of Santa Fe and Espanola (where I grew up), when
you get up high enough there are ferns on the ground, but not big ones like
that photo's! There are ferns up in the mountains toward the Santa Fe ski
run, I think, too. Not being a hiker, I only know where there are ferns you
can drive to (Lame-o me!)

Sandra
